# Example configuration for live tests against a real Splunk server.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.test` (untracked) and fill in real values:
#
#   cp .env.test.example .env.test
#
# Live tests are `#[ignore]` and run via `make test-live` / full gate `make ci`.
# If your Splunk server uses a self-signed cert, set `SPLUNK_SKIP_VERIFY=true`.
SPLUNK_BASE_URL=https://your-splunk-host:8089
SPLUNK_USERNAME=admin
SPLUNK_PASSWORD=change-me
SPLUNK_SKIP_VERIFY=true

# Live tests mode (set via environment or Makefile):
# - required: Fail if env/server unavailable (strict pre-publish gate)
# - optional: Skip with warning if unavailable (default in Makefile)
# - skip: Explicit bypass
#
# For local development without a Splunk server:
#   LIVE_TESTS_MODE=optional make test-live
#
# Fast PR gate does not run live tests:
#   make ci-fast
#
# Full CI defaults to skipping live tests:
#   make ci
# To require live tests in CI:
#   CI_LIVE_TESTS_MODE=required make ci
# LIVE_TESTS_MODE=optional
